X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Visit Davis": "https://visitdavis.org/event/art-in-bloom/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:visitdavis
X-SOURCE:Visit Davis, Visityolo Event
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260313T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260313T210000
DTSTAMP:20260309T195446
CREATED:20260224T004247Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260310T024209Z
UID:10002811-1773424800-1773435600@visitdavis.org
SUMMARY:Art in Bloom
DESCRIPTION:Art in Bloom \n  \nDates/times: March 13\, 6-9 PM\, March 14-15\, 11:30 AM – 5 PM  \nLocation: Pence Gallery\, 212 D Street\, Davis\, CA 95616 \nAdmission: Admission to the Pence is free; we welcome donations from visitors\, as they help us cover basic costs associated with running a nonprofit art gallery. \n  \nArt in Bloom is the first collaboration with members of the Davis Flower Arrangers and the Pence Gallery\, in which creative floral arrangements are paired with specific artworks on view at the Pence from March 13-15. On Friday\, March 13\, from 6-9 PM\, enjoy meeting many of the participating floral designers and see the arrangements as they are at their freshest\, as part of the city’s 2nd Friday ArtAbout reception. Visitors are welcome to enjoy a variety of arrangements that include traditional and unusual materials\, and a variety of beautiful containers. The connection between the artwork and floral design can include using similar colors\, themes\, textures\, or overall composition.  \n  \nParticipating floral designers include Janet Goehring\, Joyce Hamaguchi\, Elly Fairclough\, MJ Kelly\, Rhody Vallejo\, Elisabetta Vivoda\, Mike MacDonald\, Stephanie DeGraff-Hunt\, and Julie Haney. Each artist has chosen an artwork for inspiration\, and will create a vibrant interpretation of pieces by exhibiting artists Manuel Fernando Rios\, Barbara Prodaniuk\, and artists from Assorted Flavors\, our annual exhibit of artworks created by forty Pence members.  \n  \nFounded in 1958\, the Davis Flower Arrangers is a long-standing organization in Davis\, dedicated to studying and instructing floral design techniques\, including Ikebana. The group\, celebrating its 67th season in 2025-26\, promotes the public appreciation of floral art through workshops\, demonstrations\, and community events. For more information on the Davis Flower Arrangers\, contact President Stephanie DeGraff-Hunt at sdegraffhunt@gmail.com.  \n  \nImage: Davis Flower Arrangement (past event)
URL:https://visitdavis.org/event/art-in-bloom/
LOCATION:Pence Gallery\, 212 D Street\, Davis\, CA 95616
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visitdavis.org/wp-content/uploads/Art-in-Bloom-copy-gNSDRa.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Pence Gallery":MAILTO:pencesocialmedia@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Visit Davis": "https://visitdavis.org/event/2nd-friday-artabout-at-the-pence-gallery-12/", "Visityolo Event": "https://visityolo.com/event/2nd-friday-artabout-at-the-pence-gallery-14/"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Visit Davis": "https://visitdavis.org/event/2nd-friday-artabout-at-the-pence-gallery-12/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:visitdavis
X-SOURCE:Visit Davis, Visityolo Event
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260313T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260313T210000
DTSTAMP:20260309T195446
CREATED:20260224T004249Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260310T024209Z
UID:10002812-1773424800-1773435600@visitdavis.org
SUMMARY:2nd Friday ArtAbout at the Pence Gallery
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Pence Gallery for our 2nd Friday ArtAbout reception on March 13\, 6-9 PM in Davis. Enjoy browsing multiple art exhibits\, complimentary wine by Matchbook Wines\, and an art-themed scavenger hunt. Also\, view special floral arrangements within the exhibits by the Davis Flower Arrangers. Free admission! \n  \nManuel Fernando Rios: When They Reminisce Over You | Feb. 7 – Mar. 29 \nThe artist’s work explores his Chicano heritage\, as well as his family’s history and experiences. Blurring the line between naturalism and abstraction\, he embraces the use of complex design patterns and photography to make a powerful statement.  \n  \nAssorted Flavors: Pence Member Exhibit | Mar. 13 – Apr. 16 \nOur 2nd annual non-juried exhibit celebrates the creativity and talent of our organization’s supporters\, showcasing work in different media by 40 Pence Members. \n  \nBarbara Prodaniuk: Myths in Mud | Mar. 13 – Apr. 26 \nThe ceramic artist’s work is inspired by the forest\, meadows\, and waterways surrounding the Truckee area. She explores the stories carried by the creatures and artifacts found in these environments through layered surfaces\, organic textures\, and sculpted imagery. \n  \nLoraine Watson-Fox: Small Wonders | Mar. 6 – Mar. 29 \nThe artist employs mixed-media including collage\, text\, thread and textural elements to enhance her use of more traditional paint media. Her work is on display along the stairway. \n  \nDavis Flower Arrangers: Art in Bloom | Mar. 13 – Mar. 15 \nIn a special collaboration\, the Davis Flower Arrangers have put together creative floral arrangements to be paired with specific artworks on view at the Pence. \n  \nScavenger Hunt: Join us for a fun\, art-themed scavenger hunt at the Pence during the 2nd Friday ArtAbout. Complete all of the clues by exploring our exhibits for the chance to win a special prize. \n  \n— \n  \nVisit the Pence and other venues in Downtown Davis for the 2nd Friday ArtAbout artwalk. We will have printed ArtAbout guides available that week. Follow the ArtAbout’s Facebook page for more information: https://www.facebook.com/davisartabout. \n  \nImages: \nManuel Fernando Rios\, “Jose as Huitzilopochtli” \nBarbara Prodaniuk\, “Raven Vase” \nLoraine Watson-Fox\, “156” \nDavis Flower Arrangement (past event)
URL:https://visitdavis.org/event/2nd-friday-artabout-at-the-pence-gallery-12/
LOCATION:Pence Gallery\, 212 D Street\, Davis\, CA 95616
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://visitdavis.org/wp-content/uploads/Pence-Reception-Banners-copy-5-WClPAE.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Pence Gallery":MAILTO:pencesocialmedia@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
